1
00:00:43,060 --> 00:00:46,780
=Auspicious Nobles=

2
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,940
=Episode 21=

3
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:52,500
(No Touching, No Five-Star Review)

4
00:00:53,180 --> 00:00:55,500
(Wangshi Tower)

5
00:01:12,310 --> 00:01:13,840
Starting today,

6
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:18,710
everyone is to offer home delivery.

7
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,590
As for you two,

8
00:01:25,230 --> 00:01:26,000
you two are

9
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,280
the stars of our delivery team.

10
00:01:28,280 --> 00:01:28,920
What stars?

11
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:30,680
Besides delivering food,

12
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:33,150
you must use your charm

13
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,840
to make every madam
fall in love with our desserts.

14
00:01:36,950 --> 00:01:38,350
I'm an assassin.

15
00:01:38,950 --> 00:01:40,870
A lady killer is still a killer.

16
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,870
It's called optimizing our resources.

17
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,310
You...

18
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,450
Do you have any objections?

19
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,150
Whatever Master says,

20
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,200
I will do.

21
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:56,400
Good.

22
00:01:57,310 --> 00:01:58,280
Go make your deliveries.

23
00:02:02,230 --> 00:02:03,350
Hurry up.

24
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,360
Your double-skin milk. Please sign here.

25
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,080
Chou is here again.

26
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:21,590
Five-star review.

27
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,430
All right.

28
00:02:27,430 --> 00:02:28,910
I'll give you a five-star review.

29
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:32,660
(Double-Skin Milk. Five-Star Review)

30
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:37,590
Chou, come here!

31
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:39,870
You'd better be the one
delivering it next time.

32
00:02:39,870 --> 00:02:41,520
Your double-skin milk. Please sign.

33
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,430
Five stars.

34
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,470
Here's your money.

35
00:02:47,190 --> 00:02:49,670
Let me touch you a little longer,
and I'll give you five stars.

36
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,810
Why are there two three-star reviews?

37
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:55,430
That woman

38
00:02:56,150 --> 00:02:57,120
wanted to touch me.

39
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:00,520
You're a grown man.

40
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:02,290
Is a little touching
really going to hurt you?

41
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:03,800
Go apologize to the customer.

42
00:03:03,810 --> 00:03:05,390
Get those three-star reviews
changed to five-star reviews.

43
00:03:10,630 --> 00:03:11,680
Go now.

44
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,470
Yes, Master.

45
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,430
You used to chase me wherever I went.

46
00:03:23,430 --> 00:03:25,310
Now I'll let you see
what it's feels like

47
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:27,630
to be running around nonstop.

48
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:33,280
Your Highness, the Tower Master
has recently been declining

49
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,990
Your Highness's invitations
with one excuse after another.

50
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:36,910
The scouts reported
that she's been staying

51
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:39,080
at Wangshi Tower these past few days.

52
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,710
I have failed.

53
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,690
We were unable
to enter Wangshi Tower to investigate.

54
00:03:44,710 --> 00:03:46,680
What are your plans, Tower Master?

55
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:48,590
The Crown Prince is dead anyway.

56
00:03:49,080 --> 00:03:50,080
I'm tired too.

57
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:51,840
This is a good chance to take a break.

58
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:56,190
We can worry about making money later.

59
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:58,630
As clever as she is,

60
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,240
she's bound to have grown suspicious

61
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,400
about what happened
at the workshop that night.

62
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:05,710
That's fine.

63
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:09,030
The sooner she sees
the real me, the better.

64
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,470
After all,

65
00:04:11,030 --> 00:04:12,680
once we're truly husband and wife,

66
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,430
I can't keep pretending forever.

67
00:04:16,270 --> 00:04:17,480
Your Highness...

68
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:23,240
How is His Majesty doing?

69
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,420
Everything has gone
according to Your Highness's plan.

70
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:27,810
The ministers have been petitioning
His Majesty daily to name a new Crown Prince.

71
00:04:27,850 --> 00:04:29,360
But His Majesty simply claimed illness.

72
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:31,680
He hasn't even attended morning court
these past few days.

73
00:04:32,950 --> 00:04:34,800
He's still thinking about Yuanhe.

74
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,920
It's time to make him give up.

75
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,000
Your Majesty,

76
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:46,720
the Imperial Guards found a skeleton

77
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:48,160
among the rocks beneath the cliff.

78
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,160
Though it had
been gnawed by wild beasts,

79
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,360
it was impossible to identify.

80
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,900
But the clothing and personal belongings

81
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:56,120
were identical to those
of the Crown Prince.

82
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:58,160
What?

83
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:00,000
He?

84
00:05:00,160 --> 00:05:00,920
Your Majesty,

85
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:03,070
the dead cannot be brought back to life.

86
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:05,870
Please take care of your health.

87
00:05:06,070 --> 00:05:09,160
Your Majesty,
please accept our condolences.

88
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:17,120
Your Majesty,

89
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:20,390
although I should not
raise this matter now,

90
00:05:21,390 --> 00:05:23,560
the Crown Prince's position

91
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,950
must not remain vacant.

92
00:05:25,070 --> 00:05:27,190
I have just lost my son.

93
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:30,630
All I want now is to bring He home.

94
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:33,480
Father,

95
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:35,630
allow me to bring Yuanhe home.

96
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:36,680
No.

97
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:39,480
The Second Prince
is the best candidate for Crown Prince.

98
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,370
How can he retrieve
the remains and bury them?

99
00:05:41,390 --> 00:05:42,160
Silence!

100
00:05:42,630 --> 00:05:44,430
I have never harbored such ambitions.

101
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:48,190
Besides, Father is still
in the prime of his life.

102
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:51,000
There will surely be
more heirs in the future.

103
00:05:51,630 --> 00:05:52,600
When that time comes,

104
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,510
Father can decide then.

105
00:05:55,430 --> 00:05:57,510
Your Majesty, the Crown Prince
has just passed away.

106
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,430
The court urgently needs stability.

107
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:00,920
Among all the princes,

108
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:02,680
only the Second Prince has come of age.

109
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,240
This concerns
the foundation of the realm.

110
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,070
Please consider it carefully.

111
00:06:07,190 --> 00:06:10,680
- Please put the greater good first.
- Please put the greater good first.

112
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,920
You...

113
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,560
Zhao,

114
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,160
take men with you personally

115
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,800
to bring He home.

116
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:27,240
Then,

117
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:31,160
temporarily take He's place.

118
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,120
Father,

119
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:36,120
I am not fit for that role.

120
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,240
If I tell you to go, then go.

121
00:06:40,830 --> 00:06:41,560
Yes.

122
00:06:45,630 --> 00:06:47,480
We bid Your Majesty farewell.

123
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,800
- We bid Your Majesty farewell.
- We bid Your Majesty farewell.

124
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:07,260
(Uphold the Law with Justice)

125
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,960
Congratulations, Your Highness.

126
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,820
No, congratulations,
Your Highness the Crown Prince.

127
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:30,120
Your wish has finally come true.

128
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:33,070
The title of Crown Prince
is just a title.

129
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,480
As long as Father wishes,

130
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:37,830
he can appoint one,

131
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:39,630
or remove one.

132
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:42,000
What do you mean, Your Highness?

133
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:44,920
Hasn't Father been claiming illness?

134
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:48,190
Then let him stay ill.

135
00:07:49,070 --> 00:07:50,480
A good rest

136
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,870
will do everyone good.

137
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,270
What's this?

138
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:59,120
Are you feeding rabbits?

139
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,000
Where's the chicken?

140
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,240
There's not even any meat.

141
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,630
How is this healthy food?

142
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:08,720
This is outright abuse.

143
00:08:08,790 --> 00:08:10,750
Even on the frontier,
I never had it this bad.

144
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:11,920
This is outrageous.

145
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,150
I'm going to
the accounts office to get some money.

146
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,300
Let's eat at the restaurant.

147
00:08:16,430 --> 00:08:18,190
Young Master.

148
00:08:18,430 --> 00:08:20,240
The Young Madam said

149
00:08:20,430 --> 00:08:22,310
from now on, whenever you eat out,

150
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:23,270
if it's for official business,

151
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:25,230
you must submit
a request three days in advance.

152
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,800
Include who's attending
and the reason for the meal.

153
00:08:28,190 --> 00:08:29,800
If it's for personal matters,

154
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,870
pay for it yourself.

155
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,200
Where's my monthly allowance?

156
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:35,720
Miss Caiyuan just brought it over.

157
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,550
Two taels.

158
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:39,960
How much?

159
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,480
Two taels?

160
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:43,320
Is this supposed to keep a beggar alive?

161
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,630
The Young Madam also said

162
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:48,120
that you can stay if you want.

163
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,360
If not, you're free to leave.

164
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,120
Outrageous.

165
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:02,200
Add a little more cumin.

166
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,910
It smells amazing.

167
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:12,030
You're eating like you've been starving.

168
00:09:12,390 --> 00:09:14,390
You have no idea
how good grilled skewers are.

169
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,080
This meal isn't free.

170
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:18,360
One hundred taels.

171
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:19,630
One hundred taels?

172
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,030
Why don't you just rob me?

173
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,240
Do I look like that kind of person?

174
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,440
Robbery is against the law.

175
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:26,790
I'm running a legitimate business.

176
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,360
Li Qingqing.

177
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,670
She won't give me a single coin.

178
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:48,780
Meanwhile, she's eating
and drinking like a queen.

179
00:09:50,330 --> 00:09:51,630
And she's even got
some other man with her.

180
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:52,480
Exactly.

181
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,870
I'm going to deal with...

182
00:09:53,960 --> 00:09:54,670
Yang.

183
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:56,910
No.

184
00:09:58,150 --> 00:09:59,150
I haven't eaten yet.

185
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,120
This lamb smells amazing.

186
00:10:05,030 --> 00:10:06,390
The lamb chops smell incredible.

187
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:13,480
(Since she's locked up
all the money in the treasury,)

188
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:14,670
(I'll just...)

189
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:15,770
(I'll just steal it back.)

190
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,390
(That's the Pan family's money.)

191
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:18,960
(I'm only taking back what's ours.)

192
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,300
(How can that be called stealing?)

193
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,630
General Pan, what happened to you?

194
00:10:57,630 --> 00:10:59,270
You did this to me...

195
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:01,840
Me?

196
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:02,840
Don't! Don't move!

197
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,270
It's an anti-theft measure.

198
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:08,120
Who told you to stay up so late

199
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,550
and sneak in here like a thief?

200
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:10,390
Guards!

201
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:12,360
Take this rat back to his room.

202
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,200
Have someone treat his injuries.

203
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:15,550
And one more thing.

204
00:11:16,030 --> 00:11:18,550
Charge the medical fees to his account.

205
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,120
- Yes.
- Yes.

206
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,670
You...

207
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,600
Don't!

208
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:24,480
Easy!

209
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:26,550
Li Qingqing, just you wait!

210
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:27,510
This isn't over!

211
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,510
Move!

212
00:11:31,910 --> 00:11:33,240
Watch my foot!

213
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,270
- Boss Zhang!
- Li!

214
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,670
He's only acting so smug
because the Second Prince has his back.

215
00:11:49,670 --> 00:11:50,960
What's so impressive about that?

216
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:58,960
What's wrong?

217
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,550
Isn't that...

218
00:12:01,750 --> 00:12:02,270
Who is it?

219
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,320
Did you see him?

220
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,480
The man we just saw,

221
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,690
didn't he look like the deposed
Crown Prince Zheng Yuanhe?

222
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:09,080
You saw it too?

223
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:11,960
She's acting so arrogantly

224
00:12:12,020 --> 00:12:14,080
because she thinks
the Second Prince has her back.

225
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:15,870
The Crown Prince's death

226
00:12:15,870 --> 00:12:17,780
is the only reason
the Second Prince took his place.

227
00:12:17,870 --> 00:12:19,480
If he found out Li Qingqing was hiding

228
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:21,030
the deposed Crown Prince here,

229
00:12:21,790 --> 00:12:23,790
would he still
trust Li Qingqing so completely?

230
00:12:34,380 --> 00:12:37,740
♪Snowflakes settle gently
upon your brows♪

231
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:41,900
♪Your dark hair
brushes across my fingertips♪

232
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:44,420
♪Your smile♪

233
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:46,940
♪Melts away the winter snow♪

234
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:50,620
♪One fleeting glance says more
than a thousand words♪

235
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:54,420
♪Yet I stand before you♪

236
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:58,980
♪Unable to recognize your eyes♪

237
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:01,300
♪Though fate tries♪

238
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:03,900
♪To make us pass each other by♪

239
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:07,540
♪I choose to make our story whole♪

240
00:13:07,780 --> 00:13:09,420
♪Though time slips by♪

241
00:13:09,420 --> 00:13:11,180
♪As day turns into night♪

242
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:15,740
♪I still remember
our days at Wangshi Tower♪

243
00:13:16,140 --> 00:13:18,540
♪One glance at you lasts a lifetime♪

244
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:20,300
♪Blessed by fate♪

245
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:25,460
♪I believe this moment
will last forever♪

246
00:13:25,460 --> 00:13:27,900
♪Your smiling face♪

247
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,740
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

248
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:34,380
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

249
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:38,340
♪And wander the world together♪

250
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,700
♪Holding you close♪

251
00:13:39,700 --> 00:13:42,220
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

252
00:13:42,220 --> 00:13:44,540
♪Your tenderness♪

253
00:13:44,540 --> 00:13:47,420
♪Is the brightest moon♪

254
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:51,100
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

255
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:54,940
♪Our love will never fade away♪

256
00:13:54,940 --> 00:13:57,380
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

257
00:13:57,900 --> 00:14:02,180
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪

258
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,820
♪Your smiling face♪

259
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:16,580
♪Is the most beautiful poem♪

260
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:20,740
♪I'd rather spend my days with you♪

261
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:24,460
♪And wander the world together♪

262
00:14:24,460 --> 00:14:25,780
♪Holding you close♪

263
00:14:25,780 --> 00:14:28,420
♪Envying neither lovers nor immortals♪

264
00:14:28,420 --> 00:14:30,700
♪Your tenderness♪

265
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:33,540
♪Is the brightest moon♪

266
00:14:33,540 --> 00:14:37,300
♪I'd rather
pledge three lifetimes to you♪

267
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:41,100
♪Our love will never fade away♪

268
00:14:41,100 --> 00:14:43,740
♪Though heaven and earth grow old♪

269
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:48,140
♪My heart will remain forever pure♪
